<br>
 <p><img src=http://www.warghoul.com/images/talicsig.jpg >

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglamdrin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glamdrin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/30/01 12:30:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Agro/taunt</span><hr size=1> Well, as I said, I really hesitated to start this... in fact lets just forget that its a Wurmslayer all together. I'm just interested as to why I seemed to hold agro better with higher damage weapons as opposed to faster ones. I have a Berzerkers sword and a giant Militia Longsword... I have not tested those, but those are both very slow but higher damage one handers too. <br>
<br>
I'm just not sure if I'm experiencing that borderline area where it doesnt make as much difference what you use, or if there is anything too it. Its just my experience at lvl 41 that I hold agro better with the higher damage weapon as opposed to something that is just faster. Obviously this may change in the next few levels.<br>
<br>
-Glamdrin  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uamaretto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amaretto</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/30/01 1:17:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Agro/taunt</span><hr size=1> Personally I still think the wurmslayer works good till about 45. Unless you have access to some high end low delay weapons (like most of the people here who say the wurmslayer is the devil), the wurmslayer will be better up to that point. Now granted my restarted warrior has switched to lammies at 36, I'd still be using a wurmslayer if I all I could afford were something like ykeshas.<br>
<br>
Also, from my experience, faster delay weapons only help for aggro if you are doing comparable or better damage as a high delay weapon. Hense why you had aggro problems at 41 with the Sap and Yak. Copelands shows that combo as doing 570 DPM (no haste, 150str). While Wurm and Sap gets 676. 100+ more damage per minute is a pretty big difference. Now, at 41 with dual lammies, interestingly you get the exact same 676DPM....guess which one will taunt better? Lammies. If you want a cheaper combo that would do similar damage, try a jarsath trident and cane of the tranquil. You'd probably have much better success with those.<br>
<br>
I think alot of people seem to overlook is damage does make a difference, to a point. Especially pre 50. Now granted when I see a 50+ warrior using a Wurmslayer, I laugh somewhat. But before that I really don't see a problem with it.<br>
<br>
Just use the damn wurm if it still works. When it stops working, switch. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usinark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinark</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/31/01 7:40:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Agro/taunt</span><hr size=1> According to copelands, Wurm + lammy outdamages dual lammies until 45, and does roughly the same amount of damage until 51. Personally, I didn't have too much trouble taunting when I used a wurmslayer. It all depends on who you're taunting off really. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglamdrin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glamdrin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/31/01 8:13:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Agro/taunt</span><hr size=1> Well thanks guys for responding. I know you dont like WS Talic, but thanks for the input <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  This was just more for curiosity than anything. I know a lot of this is just experimentation anyways, and I guess I'll just keep using what I can until I get something better.<br>
<br>
-Glamdrin   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaerildroigheann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeril Droigheann</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/31/01 11:31:50 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.freshpope.com/gfx/ctree2sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Agro/taunt</span><hr size=1> Before 50 you can taunt with a rusty spoon.  It's after 50 where you start running into problems and need to rely on procs, speed and proximity.  Especially when the mobs themselves are over 50. <p>~Tunare's Enforcer~<br>
<a href="http://interealms.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=4080">Aeril Droigheann</a>, 59 Preserver<br>
<a href="http://interealms.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=4050">Aeryl Firebrand</a>, Warlord<br>
<a href="http://interealms.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=11522">Aerul Cuinnsear</a>, 46 Rogue<br>
Undaunted, Xegony<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ulavarac.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lavarac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/31/01 11:43:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Agro/taunt</span><hr size=1> Use what works... it was real simple. You couldn't hold agro with weapon set &quot;A&quot; so you switched to &quot;B&quot; and had no problem. If you can carry all the weapons around, it's as simple as that.<br>
<br>
For me, I use an IBC/CoT combo and usually have no problem holding agro. If I'm not the main assist I'll more than likely swap out the IBC for something else and that most times takes care of the agro issue.<br>
<br>
My experience says that fast primary (yet still decent damage) gives me the most agro. Your experience says otherwise. Until someone cracks the hate code, I don't think we'll have a definitive answer.<br>
<br>
Good luck to you,<br>
-Lavarac Steelwolf 45 warrior<br>
